Information
------------------------------

Supercar Megabuild
In every episode our British motor-mad mechanics will embark on an ambitious mission to transform an ordinary car into extraordinary supercar.
But with limited time and other inevitable roadblocks piling on the pressure, will they succeed in creating the ultimate supercars?


1)  Aston Martin Vantage v8 
Mechanics undertake extreme car engineering challenges, beginning by transforming an Aston Martin into a supercharged racing car that is also road legal.

2)  Rolls Royce Silver Shadow 
Shane Lynch challenges the crew to transform his Rolls Royce into a drift racer, an assignment that takes them to Japan, home of the unusual motor sport.

3)  Range Rover Evoque 
The team converts a Range Rover into a custom off-roader, then puts it to the ultimate test by driving it through the dunes of the Sahara desert.

4)  Mercedes G Wagen 
Engineers Ralph Hosier and Ranen Rudra modify a car for one of their mentor's clients to make it more secure.

5)  Jeep Wrangler 
Afzal sets the engineers their toughest challenge to date - to create a Jeep that is bigger and better than any that have gone before it.

6)  Nissan GTR 
Afzal Kahn challenges engineers Ralph and Ranen to engineer a car to beat his Bugatti Veyron in a straight quarter-mile race.

7)  Porsche Panamera 
Under the eye of motoring mogul Afzal Kahn, engineers Ralph and Ranen turn a Porsche Panamera into an eco-friendly, high performance supercar.

8)  Bentley Mulsanne 
In this episode, motoring mogul Afzal Kahn is asked to help an old friend who wants to be able to go hunting in his Â£200,000 Bentley Mulsanne.

9)  Chevrolet Camaro 
Automotive engineers Ralph Hosier and Ranen Rudra are on a mission to bring an American muscle car to the UK.

10)  Audi A8 
Engineers Ralph and Ranen are tasked with producing a vehicle able to survive winter conditions, take on difficult terrain... and cross deep snow.
